Aneel Bhusri: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 4:11 AM ET
Software

Company Overview of Workday, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Aneel   Bhusri  Co-Founder, Chief Executive Officer and Director, Workday, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 10 Board Members in 10 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships51$2,200,612As of Fiscal Year 2017
Background

		Mr. Aneel Bhusri Co-founded Workday, Inc. in March 2005 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since May 13, 2014. Mr. Bhusri is an Advisory Partner at Greylock Partners, where he was previously a Partner. He joined Greylock in April 1999. As an Advisory Partner at the Greylock, he has been an active investor in cloud technologies, with an emphasis on applications, data center infrastructure and middleware. He served as a Co-Chief Executive Officer of Workday, Inc. ... from September 2009 to May 13, 2014 and its Chairman from January 2012 to May 13, 2014. He served as the President at Workday, Inc. until September 9, 2009 and also served as its Chief Vision Officer. He started his technology career in the early 1990s at PeopleSoft. Mr. Bhusri served as Vice Chairman of PeopleSoft Inc. from 1999 to 2004 and a Consultant since September 2004. He served as Senior Vice President of Product Strategy, Business Development and Marketing, from June 1998 to January 1999. Mr. Bhusri was responsible for developing and guiding all product strategy, corporate and product marketing at the company. He led the PeopleSoft's business development efforts in key areas such as new product development, vertical market initiatives and corporate expansion. Prior to PeopleSoft, he held positions in both venture capital and corporate finance. Mr. Bhusri served as an Associate at Norwest Venture Partners and spent several years in Morgan Stanley's corporate finance organization working with the Morgan Stanley's high-tech clients. From April 1995 to November 1995, he served as the Vice President of Product Strategy and from August 1993 to April 1995, as the Director of Product Strategy. Mr. Bhusri serves as Chairman of Drobo, Inc and has been its Director since October 25, 2005. He served as the Chairman of OutlookSoft Corporation since May 11, 2005. He served as the Chairman of Cape Clear Software Inc. and PolyServe, Inc. He served as Chairman of Data Domain, Inc., since March 2007 and also as its Director, since February 2002 and as a Lead Investor. Mr. Bhusri has been a Director of Workday, Inc. since 2005 and Pure Storage, Inc. since July 2010. He serves as a Director of The Tech Museum of Innovation, Illuminator Inc., Cape Clear, Symhoniq, Simply Continuous, Inc., Data Robotics, Cameraworld.com, Software Development Forum, Above All Software, Inc. and served as Cloudera, Inc. until December 14, 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Intel Corporation since June 20, 2014 and has been its Independent Lead Director since May 18, 2017. Mr. Bhusri has been a Director of Okta, Inc. from August 8, 2011 to December 2016. He served as Director of Tidemark Systems, Inc.  Mr. Bhusri serves as a Member of the Advisory Board of Northern Light Venture Capital. He served on the Board of Directors of PeopleSoft since March 1999. He served as a Member of Advisory Board of Elementum SCM, Inc. since April 8, 2014. Mr. Bhusri served as a Director of Sumo Logic, Inc. He also served on the Board of Pertigo. He served as a Director of PolyServe, Inc. and Symphoniq Corporation. He served as a Director of Marimba Inc. since February 1999. He served as a Director of Syniverse Brience LLC, since September 2000. He served as a Director of Corio Inc., from April 1999 to May 12, 2004 and OutlookSoft Corporation since May 2005. Mr. Bhusri served on the Boards of SeeBeyond Technology Corp., HelloAsia, Inc., Perfigo, Inc., Vantive and Guru Worldwide, Inc. He has been a leader, product visionary and innovator in the enterprise software industry for more than 20 years. He was named to the Forbes Midas List in 2014 (#14), 2013 (#17), 2012 (#25), 2011 (#15), 2009 (#8) and 2008 (#16) and to the AlwaysOn Top 100 List of VCs in 2009. Mr. Bhusri is ranked 15th on the 2011 Forbes Midas List, the Top Tech Investors. He holds an M.B.A. Degree from the Graduate School of Business at Stanford University and a B.S. in Electrical Engineering and BA in Economics from Brown University.Read Full Background




